<header class="header">
  <h1>Best Seed Company for Short Season Gardens</h1>
  <p class="tagline">
    If your season is short, the seed company you choose matters more than the crop.
  </p>
  <p class="lede">
    <strong>For most short-season gardeners, Johnny’s Selected Seeds, West Coast Seeds, and Territorial Seed are the strongest starting points because they consistently offer earlier varieties, clearer maturity data, and more reliable performance in limited growing windows.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    In a long season, almost anything will eventually produce. In a short season, many crops never reach maturity at all.
  </p>
  <p>
    The difference is not effort — it’s choosing seeds that actually fit your timeline.
  </p>
</header>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Quick Picks: Best Seed Companies for Short Seasons</h2>

  <div class="quickAnswerBox">
    <ul class="plainList">
      <li><strong>Best overall:</strong> Johnny’s Selected Seeds — strongest balance of early varieties and reliable data.</li>
      <li><strong>Best for cool climates:</strong> West Coast Seeds — excellent selection for northern and coastal conditions.</li>
